One-shot sentinel: while this file exists, the deploy restores ~/.hermes/state.db
from the LARGEST state.db.wiped.<timestamp> backup on the VM (the one holding the
real, pre-wipe conversations — later re-wipes only archived an empty db).

Guarded by an on-VM marker (~/.hermes/.restored) so it runs at most once even if
this file lingers. The current db is preserved as state.db.prerestore.<ts> and the
backup is kept (copied, not moved). Restoring is safe now that session_search and
memory are disabled — old per-user data cannot re-open the cross-user leak.

Remove this file in a follow-up commit once the restore has run.
